Slide 1 of 3Ariarne Titmus retiresFour-time Olympian Ariarne Titmus has announced her retirement at the age of 25. Titmus says it is tough to retire but she is comfortable with the decision. 

 Titmus will finish her career as one of the greatest distance swimmers of all time.

Slide 1 of 3Hostage release Hamas has handed over the last remaining Israeli hostages in Gaza.

 The hostages were handed over to the Red Cross and escorted by the IDF for medical evaluation.

 

 

 Donald Trump has flown to Israel to meet with families of the hostages in Tel Aviv.

Slide 1 of 3Diane Keaton Diane Keaton, the Oscar-winning star of Annie Hall, has died aged 79.Keaton's career began in the late 1970s and included starring in more than 100 films. 

 


 Keaton died in California and is survived by her two children, Dexter and Duke.

Slide 1 of 3Qantas cyber attackPersonal data of Qantas customers has been released on the dark web.

 Up to six million Qantas customer records were exposed in July during a cyber attack on a third-party platform.

 Qantas says it is investigating.

Slide 1 of 3Tariffs Donald Trump has threatened to place an additional 100 per cent tax on Chinese imports.

 It follows China's decision to restrict foreign access to rare earth minerals.

 The fresh tensions between the world's two largest economies will have repercussions on global markets.

Slide 1 of 3Rap beefDrake has lost his lawsuit over Kendrick Lamar's diss track Not Like Us.Drake alleged Lamar's track contained false claims he was interested in underage girls.

 But a judge found a reasonable listener would understand the track was 'hyperbolic'.
